Have you tried writing a basic outline before/while you write the story? I know it seems like an extra bullshit step, but if you're semi-serious about this whole writing thing, I'd recommend it.
Nothing too detailed or anything, just basic plot and story points that you'd like to cover. Makes it easy to see the big picture and edit stuff around quickly. They also help if you get an idea for where to take the story while writing, allowing you to jot it down before your mind moves on to something else. Just give it a shot as you write your next chapter or two and see how it works for you.
